<div class="tooltip">
    <p>1) You will receive a $100 statement credit with this bonus offer. You will qualify for and receive your bonus after your first use of the card. First use includes using your Account for purchases or balance transfers, or using any checks that access your Account; cash advances are not included. After qualifying, please allow 6 to 8 weeks for statement credit to post to your Account. To be eligible for this bonus offer, Account must be open and not in default at the time of fulfillment. This one-time bonus offer is valid only for first-time Cardmembers with new Accounts. Previous and existing Cardmembers/Accounts are not eligible for this bonus offer.</p>
    <p>2) Participation in the program allows you to enjoy the benefits of the GM Business Card World MasterCard®, including the ability to accumulate "Earnings." You will accumulate earnings at a rate of 5% for each $1 of net purchases made on dealership parts and service at authorized GM Vehicle Dealers. You will accumulate Earnings at a rate of 3% for each $1 of net purchases made at merchants that classify their merchant locations for MasterCard in any of the following categories: dining establishments, office supply stores and wholesale distributors, gas at the pump. You will accumulate Earnings at a rate of 1% for each $1 of all other net purchases. We do not determine whether merchants correctly identify and bill transactions as being made at locations in each particular category. However, we do reserve the right to determine which purchases qualify for the 3% Earnings. Purchases not eligible to receive 3% Earnings include, but are not limited to, purchases made at superstores, warehouse clubs, discount stores and their affiliates. Online and catalog purchases are not eligible to receive 3% Earnings unless the merchants have correctly identified and billed the transactions. You do not accumulate Earnings on balance transfers; cash advances; cash-like charges such as travelers checks, foreign currency and money orders; any checks that are used to access your Account; overdraft advances; interest; unauthorized or fraudulent charges; or fees of any kind, including fees for products that protect or insure the balances of your Account. There is no maximum number of Earnings that you can accumulate in the program. See Rewards Program Rules and Regulations that will be mailed after your Account is established.</p>
</div>


